"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The OneHotEncoder in scikit-learn does not directly support string input. It requires integer input, such as the output of LabelEncoder or OrdinalEncoder. Therefore, the correct way to preprocess categorical data is to use LabelEncoder or OrdinalEncoder before OneHotEncoder.\", \"patch\": \"20,21c20,22\\n< ('numeric', MinMaxScaler(), ['a']),\\n< ('categoric', OneHotEncoder(), [\\\"b\\\"])\\n---\\n> ('numeric', MinMaxScaler(), ['a']),\\n> ('categoric', Pipeline([('label', LabelEncoder()), ('onehot', OneHotEncoder())]), [\\\"b\\\"])\\n> from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\\n\"}"